[[Image:White-Pine-Trail-State-Park-Map.gif|thumb|right|The path of the White Pine Trail]]
 
The trail extends from Ann Street in Grand Rapids north to Cadillac. The trail has three paved sections: one extending {{convert|22|mi|km}} between [[Comstock Park, Michigan|Comstock Park]] and [[Sand Lake, Michigan|Sand Lake]], another {{convert|13|mi|km|adj=on}} stretch between [[Big Rapids, Michigan|Big Rapids]] and [[Reed City, Michigan|Reed City]], and a 16 mile stretch between Leroy and Cadillac. The Michigan DNR has plans to pave {{convert|7.6|mi|km}} of trail from Russel Road near Cedar Springs to Sand Lake during the summer of 2007.(Completed)
